</div></div></div><div class="anchorable docEntry" id="method_setheaders_0"><div class="docEntryHeader"><code class="inline-code-block"><a href="#method_setheaders_0" class="anchor-link" aria-label="Anchor" tabindex="-1">#</a><a class="font-bold font-lg link" href="../.././http/~/OutgoingMessage.prototype.setHeaders">setHeaders</a><span class="font-medium">(<span><span>headers<span>: <span><span>Headers</span><span> | </span><span>Map</span>&lt;<span>string</span><span>, </span><div class="ml-indent"><span><span>number</span></span><br /><span><span> | </span><span>string</span></span><br /><span><span> | </span><span>readonly</span> <span>string</span>[]</span></div>&gt;</span></span></span></span>)<span>: <span>this</span></span></span></code> </div><div class="max-w-[75ch]"><div data-color-mode="dark" data-light-theme="light" data-dark-theme="dark" class="markdown-body"><p>Sets multiple header values for implicit headers. headers must be an instance of
<code>Headers</code> or <code>Map</code>, if a header already exists in the to-be-sent headers, its
